entry.title: lambdaclass/cairo-vm_in_C
entry.summary: cairo-vm_in_C is a C implementation of the Cairo VM. Cairo (CPU Algebraic Intermediate Representation) is a programming language for writing provable programs, where one party can prove to another that a certain computation was executed correctly without the need for this party to re-execute the same program.
